The factor to maximize is \( (1+2\gamma)^{1/2}(1-\gamma)^{1/2} \), which is equivalent to maximizing \( (1+2\gamma)(1-\gamma) \).  
Expanding gives \( 1 + 2\gamma - \gamma - 2\gamma^2 = 1 + \gamma - 2\gamma^2 \), and taking the derivative yields \( 1 - 4\gamma = 0 \), so \( \gamma = 0.25 \).  

